import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['precipitation'].plot(kind='hist', bins=30, color='blue', edgecolor='black', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['precipitation'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['precipitation'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['precipitation'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['precipitation'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of precipitation in Seattle?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['temp_max'])
    plt.title('How does the maximum temperature vary over time in Seattle?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Maximum Temperature')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    plt.title('What is the relationship between wind and temperature in Seattle?', wrap=True)

    return plt;
